{"word":"Rahab","slug":"rahab","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Rahab</b> <a href=\"#/H7294\">H7294</a><br/><a href=\"#/H7343\">H7343</a> <br/> 1. Called Rachab, a woman of Jericho:<br/> - Assists the spies of Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=2'>Jos 2</a> <br/> - Is spared at the taking of Jericho<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=6&verse=25'>Jos 6:25</a> <br/> - Ancestor of Joseph<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=1&verse=5'>Mat 1:5</a> <br/> - Faith of, commended<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=58&chapter=11&verse=31'>Heb 11:31</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=59&chapter=2&verse=25'>Jas 2:25</a> <br/> 2. A symbolic name applied to Egypt<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=87&verse=4'>Psa 87:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=89&verse=10'>Psa 89:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=30&verse=7'>Isa 30:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=51&verse=9'>Isa 51:9</a>"}]}